ritative history of the labour movement in Lebanon is vital reading for scholars of trade unionism, Lebanese politics, and political economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLabor movementzLebanon. 0aLebanon-Politics and government-1990-. 4aPolitical Studies 2022. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh  aGeneral Confederation of Workers.  aLebanese Civil War.  aLebanese Communist Party.  aLebanese Labour Code.  aLebanese Troika.  aLebanese labour movement.  aOctober Revolution.  aSectarian power-sharing.  aSectarianism.  aUnion Coordination Committee.1 aKhater, Lea Bou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615944140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526159441423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526159441/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles